{
  "texts": [
    "The perspective is timely given the intermingling of LLMs and search engines (Nakano et al. 2021; Microsoft 2023; Tong 2024) and the question of how everyday users interact with them (Zamfirescu-Pereira et al. 2023).",
    "As LLMs are integrated into search engines, there is a need to represent both chat as well as autocompletion-style benchmarks for adverse impact evaluation.",
    "Contributions In this study, we 1) focus on stereotyping harms in open-ended generation which we deem underrepresented in current LLM evaluation suites.",
    "2) We draw on interdisciplinary scholarship, namely search engine studies, to investigate stereotyping (§3.1).",
    "We focus on autocompletestyle prompts in the style of toxicity research (Dhamala et al. 2021; Gehman et al. 2020) to evaluate these harms in open-ended generation with LLMs."
  ]
}